       char* pam_getenv (pam_handle_t *pamh, const char *name);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       pam_getenv returns a pointer to a character array contain-
       ing the value of the named PAM environment variable.   The
       application  should  free  the memory that the PAM library
       allocates to hold the returned value.  This function takes
       the  following  arguments:  (In) The authentication handle
       returned by (In) The identifier of the  environment  vari-
       able whose value is to be obtained.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       If   the   specified   PAM  environment  variable  exists,
       pam_getenv returns a pointer to  a  character  array  that
       contains its value.  Otherwise, it returns a null pointer.

